Reasoning: The paper introduces basic notions of category theory and their applications to computer science, with a focus on coalgebras. This makes it likely to belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CT (Computational Topology), cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). However, given the emphasis on coalgebras and their applications to modal logics, cs.LO is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses monads in Haskell, which could place it in cs.PL or cs.SE. Finally, the examples and applications are drawn from stochastic systems, which could suggest cs.AI as another possible sub-category.
